FBIS3-5575 "dreas046_i_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-046 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Mar 1994 Cambodia Khieu Samphan Sends Telegram to King Sihanouk BK0903043194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 8 Mar 94 BK0903043194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia Language: Cambodian Article Type:BFN [Telegram from Khieu Samphan to King Norodom Sihanouk voicing support for the royal statement dated 7 March -- read by announcer] [Text] To His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, king of the Kingdom of Cambodia. Your Majesty: I and all members of the Party of Democratic Kampuchea [PDK] have received with great pleasure your majesty's statement dated 7 March 1994. The PDK has the great honor and pleasure to voice its full support for the content of the statement. The PDK is convinced that our entire nation and people will certainly march behind Your Majesty so that you will be able to fulfill your five-point guideline. Please forgive any inappropriateness. [Dated] 8 March 1994 [Signed] Khieu Samphan, head of the PDK
